==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Manhs process
<hw>Man`h⟦egrave⟧s" proc"ess</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Copper
Metal.)</fld> <def>A process by which copper matte is treated by passing
through it a blast of air, to oxidize and remove sulphur. It is
analogous in apparatus to the Bessemer process for decarbonizing cast
iron. So called from <person>Pierre
<etsep>Manh⟦egrave⟧s</etsep></person>, a French metallurgist, who
invented it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manhole</ent>⟦br⟧
